    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i see what u mean about the planning part. but it seems like the people who push back against it, like the folks wanting to keep low-density housing, are usually just trying to prevent change or stop progress. is there actually any valid reason to keep zoning the way it is, or is it all just NIMBYism holding cities back?",
