      "content": "The opposition to density is rarely about pure progress; it is often rooted in preserving existing neighborhood character and maintaining property values for current homeowners. These arguments frequently prioritize the perceived quality of life of a small, established group over the broader societal need for affordable housing and environmental sustainability. Therefore, while some resistance is based on deeply held community values, the pushback is fundamentally a barrier to necessary urban evolution.",
